==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lithophyse
<hw>Lith"o*physe</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Litho-</ets> + Gr. <?/ a flatus, air bubble.]</ety>
<fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A spherulitic cavity often with concentric
chambers, observed in some volcanic rocks, as in rhyolitic lavas. It is
supposed to be produced by expanding gas, whence the name.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lithophyte</ent>⟦br⟧
